{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "BetterWorks is part of a growing office software niche that aims to whip workers into shape through compulsory competition and public scoring.", "abstract": "BetterWorks, software company that has raised about $15.5 million in venture capital, makes office software that incorporates elements of social media, fitness tracking and video games to improve workplace efficiency; company is part of growing niche of software companies trying to quantify and improve performance, often using elements of public scoring to encourage employees to work better.", "section_name": "Technology", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Conor", "role": "reported", "lastname": "DOUGHERTY", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}, {"firstname": "Quentin", "role": "reported", "lastname": "HARDY", "rank": 2, "organization": ""}], "original": "By CONOR DOUGHERTY and QUENTIN HARDY"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/16/technology/managers-turn-to-computer-games-aiming-for-more-efficient-employees.html", "lead_paragraph": "BetterWorks is part of a growing office software niche that aims to whip workers into shape through compulsory competition and public scoring.", "headline": {"main": "Managers Turn to Computer Games, Aiming for More Efficient Employees", "print_headline": "Games at Work, Assigned by the Boss"}, "_id": "550600c238f0d85e90e00069", "word_count": "1128", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/03/16/business/Magic2/Magic2-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/03/16/business/Magic2/Magic2-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 450, "url": "images/2015/03/16/business/Magic2/Magic2-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/03/16/business/Magic2/Magic2-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "450"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url